{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d63b5a73-a1d4-4d37-b168-b779265fccae","content":"Yes, you'll run into compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 drops support for older target frameworks.** Specifically:\n\n- **`net462`** – MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework **4.7.2** (`net472`).\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** – MSTest v3 requires at minimum **.NET 6.0** (`net6.0`).\n- **`net5.0`** – Also unsupported; you'd need at least `net6.0`.\n\n**To migrate successfully, you'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to something like:**\n\n```\nnet472;net6.0\n```\n\n(or newer, e.g., `net8.0`)\n\n**Summary of required changes:**\n\n| Current TFM | Issue | Minimum for MSTest v3 |\n|---|---|---|\n| `net462` | Too old | `net472` |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | Unsupported | `net6.0` |\n| `net5.0` | Unsupported | `net6.0` |\n\nIf you can't drop those older frameworks, you'll need to stay on MSTest v2. Want me to update the project for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"72c9ff9f-01c4-4471-8cbf-edabc37f5a83","outputTokens":298,"requestId":"EC0D:1007E7:6329349:6BB20FD:6A034C1B"},"id":"06cf470f-d7ae-46de-963e-38b42539dc51","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:49:58.857Z","parentId":"36c9ab4a-8536-45e8-91d6-71a50ce8ce83"}
